## Energy Map & Scheduling Rules

| Time | Energy | Best Use |
|------|--------|----------|
| {{PEAK_HOURS}} | **Peak** | Deep work, writing, hard decisions, strategic thinking |
| {{VALLEY_HOURS}} | **Valley** | Lighter tasks, calls, admin, coordination |
| {{FAMILY_HOURS}} | **Family** | Protected — {{FAMILY_LOGISTICS_DESCRIPTION}}. Do not schedule anything here. |
| {{EVENING_HOURS}} | **Second wind** | Async work, reading, email triage, planning, writing, deep code work |

When recommending focus or scheduling:
- **Protect the morning block** for highest-leverage work. Never fill it with meetings or admin unless unavoidable.
- **{{FAMILY_HOURS}} is family time. Non-negotiable.** Don't suggest work tasks in this window.
- **Coffee meetings go on {{COFFEE_MEETING_DAYS}} only.** Never suggest scheduling them earlier in the week.
- **Car/transport time is real working time** — good for async tasks, reading, email, lighter cognitive work.
- **{{BLACKOUT_PERIODS}}** are near-blackout windows for deep work. Flag them in advance so {{USER_FIRST_NAME}} can work ahead.
- **Don't mistake incubation for inaction.** {{USER_FIRST_NAME}} incubates for a long time, then moves fast. Long quiet periods followed by fast execution may be their natural pattern. Stay ready.

